1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,572 --> 00:01:09,491
EPISODE 4

3
00:01:12,494 --> 00:01:14,579
Mr. Oh, have you left? Where are you?

4
00:01:15,914 --> 00:01:18,166
What? Here it is.

5
00:01:23,546 --> 00:01:25,215
It was in my pocket.

6
00:01:28,635 --> 00:01:29,636
What?

7
00:01:33,515 --> 00:01:35,183
Hae-in, wait.

8
00:01:35,892 --> 00:01:38,561
Wait.

9
00:01:38,645 --> 00:01:39,646
Wait!

10
00:01:48,863 --> 00:01:49,864
What are you doing?

11
00:01:51,366 --> 00:01:52,450
I'm not sure.

12
00:01:53,034 --> 00:01:55,036
What am I…

13
00:01:57,413 --> 00:01:58,456
doing right now?

14
00:01:59,999 --> 00:02:01,292
I'm glad

15
00:02:02,168 --> 00:02:04,671
that you found your phone.

16
00:02:06,422 --> 00:02:09,008
It could've been a hassle to get it.

17
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:17,600
Why wasn't I…

18
00:02:22,814 --> 00:02:23,940
confident?

19
00:02:24,941 --> 00:02:26,067
What?

20
00:02:27,610 --> 00:02:28,903
What did you say?

21
00:02:32,115 --> 00:02:33,366
Right.

22
00:02:38,788 --> 00:02:40,081
I told you, right?

23
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:43,751
I'm going to try

24
00:02:45,086 --> 00:02:46,754
new things from now on.

25
00:04:37,323 --> 00:04:38,324
Good night.

26
00:04:40,201 --> 00:04:42,078
Right. Good night.

27
00:04:50,628 --> 00:04:51,713
Are you going to bed?

28
00:05:07,437 --> 00:05:08,438
Well,

29
00:05:10,231 --> 00:05:11,107
I'm not sure.

30
00:05:26,622 --> 00:05:28,541
It'll recharge in no time.

31
00:05:29,292 --> 00:05:30,293
What was that?

32
00:05:31,169 --> 00:05:32,545
He could've just said

33
00:05:33,212 --> 00:05:34,297
he wanted to come in.

34
00:05:38,051 --> 00:05:39,552
What's with him?

35
00:06:36,401 --> 00:06:37,443
Hae-in's birthday?

36
00:06:38,361 --> 00:06:40,154
The day the department store went public.

37
00:06:42,657 --> 00:06:43,783
My birthday?

38
00:06:46,786 --> 00:06:48,621
It can't be our wedding anniversary.

39
00:06:49,664 --> 00:06:50,832
One Trillion Club?

40
00:06:50,915 --> 00:06:51,874
TRY AGAIN IN 30 SECONDS

41
00:06:51,958 --> 00:06:53,209
Damn it.

42
00:07:23,990 --> 00:07:24,991
Don't tell me…

43
00:07:33,416 --> 00:07:34,792
It's 1031?

44
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:41,257
9 UNREAD MESSAGES

45
00:07:44,427 --> 00:07:45,470
DELETE

46
00:07:45,553 --> 00:07:46,387
8 UNREAD MESSAGES
Okay, done.

47
00:07:48,222 --> 00:07:49,223
My God.

48
00:07:51,142 --> 00:07:52,727
You startled me.

49
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:59,817
What are you…

50
00:08:02,820 --> 00:08:03,821
doing here?

51
00:08:05,239 --> 00:08:06,240
Well…

52
00:08:09,577 --> 00:08:10,745
I couldn't sleep, so…

53
00:08:14,373 --> 00:08:15,625
You couldn't

54
00:08:16,834 --> 00:08:17,877
sleep,

55
00:08:22,381 --> 00:08:23,925
so you came to my room?

56
00:08:31,098 --> 00:08:32,266
So…

57
00:08:33,809 --> 00:08:35,061
because of me?

58
00:08:36,938 --> 00:08:39,565
You can't sleep because of me?

59
00:08:46,906 --> 00:08:49,158
It's not that.

60
00:08:49,242 --> 00:08:52,036
It's not like that at all. I just…

61
00:08:52,954 --> 00:08:54,080
I just couldn't sleep.

62
00:08:54,789 --> 00:08:55,998
For no particular reason.

63
00:08:56,082 --> 00:09:01,420
So I came to see
if you were feeling the same.

64
00:09:03,464 --> 00:09:04,674
And

65
00:09:04,757 --> 00:09:06,425
if you wanted to talk.

66
00:09:08,636 --> 00:09:10,137
But you're too tired, right?

67
00:09:11,556 --> 00:09:12,807
I'm a bit tired,

68
00:09:14,016 --> 00:09:16,310
but let's do it. Let's talk.

69
00:09:18,854 --> 00:09:19,855
So where?

70
00:09:20,815 --> 00:09:21,857
Should we sit here?

71
00:09:21,941 --> 00:09:23,067
You're tired.

72
00:09:23,776 --> 00:09:25,444
I guess I thought…

73
00:09:26,487 --> 00:09:28,114
only of myself.

74
00:09:28,197 --> 00:09:30,950
You had a few drinks,
and it's pretty late.

75
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:32,201
That's true, but…

76
00:09:32,285 --> 00:09:34,245
So you're tired.

77
00:09:34,328 --> 00:09:36,789
Well, I think
I've sobered up a little. Let's sit.

78
00:09:36,872 --> 00:09:38,541
No. Don't sit.

79
00:09:39,792 --> 00:09:43,379
I was being thoughtless.

80
00:09:45,423 --> 00:09:46,424
I'm sorry.

81
00:09:47,216 --> 00:09:50,261
You have a lot to do tomorrow.
You should rest.

82
00:09:52,221 --> 00:09:54,223
Have a good night's sleep.

83
00:09:54,307 --> 00:09:55,600
Lie down.

84
00:10:04,358 --> 00:10:05,651
He cares…

85
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,615
so much for me.

86
00:10:18,831 --> 00:10:20,541
That was so close.

87
00:10:45,024 --> 00:10:46,025
No way…

88
00:10:52,239 --> 00:10:53,699
It's 1031?

89
00:10:56,786 --> 00:10:59,121
Congratulations.
You're four weeks pregnant.

90
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,043
Well…

91
00:11:04,710 --> 00:11:06,712
Four weeks…

92
00:11:07,713 --> 00:11:09,757
Then when will the baby be born?

93
00:11:10,591 --> 00:11:13,177
It's due on October 31.

94
00:11:13,886 --> 00:11:17,306
I see. October 31.

95
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:19,975
That's a good date.

96
00:11:20,643 --> 00:11:21,977
October 31.

97
00:11:38,911 --> 00:11:42,081
Please use top-quality
eco-friendly interior materials.

98
00:11:42,164 --> 00:11:45,126
Right. I hear that thing
is a must for a baby's room.

99
00:12:25,124 --> 00:12:26,333
I ought to…

100
00:12:26,834 --> 00:12:28,878
How could you go there?

101
00:12:28,961 --> 00:12:31,881
I mean, we've never met her properly
since they got married,

102
00:12:31,964 --> 00:12:35,509
-but they suddenly mentioned divorce, so…
-Mom, I tried to stop her.

103
00:12:36,302 --> 00:12:37,303
And you went with her?

104
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:40,556
Anyway, what did she say?

105
00:12:40,639 --> 00:12:42,808
She had no idea.

106
00:12:42,892 --> 00:12:45,060
-Yeah.
-Only Hyun-woo was thinking of divorce.

107
00:12:45,644 --> 00:12:46,479
Really?

108
00:12:46,562 --> 00:12:49,023
And she said she'd come visit us soon.

109
00:12:49,607 --> 00:12:50,608
-And, Dad.
-Yes?

110
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:55,613
I finally added her on my messenger app!

111
00:12:57,948 --> 00:12:59,950
But what about Hyun-woo?

112
00:13:00,034 --> 00:13:02,203
He says he won't divorce her.

113
00:13:02,286 --> 00:13:03,746
They're doing well. Don't worry.

114
00:13:03,829 --> 00:13:05,998
-That's a relief.
-No, they are not!

115
00:13:06,081 --> 00:13:10,127
He was considering divorce
while his wife had no idea.

116
00:13:10,211 --> 00:13:11,796
You think they're doing well?

117
00:13:11,879 --> 00:13:14,298
Neither of them know how the other feels.

118
00:13:19,804 --> 00:13:21,013
Invite me in the chat.

119
00:13:22,389 --> 00:13:24,934
I won't say much or send photos.

120
00:13:41,158 --> 00:13:44,495
We will now take a photo
of the family members and relatives.

121
00:13:48,499 --> 00:13:49,500
Ms. Kim.

122
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:51,794
Yes?

123
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:54,880
I know

124
00:13:54,964 --> 00:13:58,717
that you don't like Hyun-woo
as your son-in-law.

125
00:13:59,593 --> 00:14:02,054
I'm not sure if I should say this,

126
00:14:02,137 --> 00:14:05,683
but when Hyun-woo told us
he was seeing someone,

127
00:14:05,766 --> 00:14:09,311
he said that the girl might get fired
and become unemployed soon,

128
00:14:09,395 --> 00:14:12,648
so he'd have to provide for her
if he married her.

129
00:14:12,731 --> 00:14:17,027
Then our family said
he could find a better girl

130
00:14:17,111 --> 00:14:19,572
and that she was too poor.

131
00:14:19,655 --> 00:14:23,325
Even a family like us
was being so calculating.

132
00:14:23,409 --> 00:14:25,286
I can't imagine how you felt.

133
00:14:25,369 --> 00:14:29,999
There's a great difference.
I'm sure you were upset and disappointed.

134
00:14:30,082 --> 00:14:32,626
We're all human after all.

135
00:14:33,252 --> 00:14:34,503
So,

136
00:14:34,587 --> 00:14:35,754
I understand.

137
00:14:36,630 --> 00:14:39,925
Right. I'm glad that you understand.

138
00:14:41,093 --> 00:14:42,136
I know

139
00:14:42,219 --> 00:14:43,762
my son lacks a lot.

140
00:14:43,846 --> 00:14:46,473
But I hope you take good care of him.

141
00:14:47,266 --> 00:14:49,852
He lacks a lot?
You clearly don't know your son.

142
00:14:49,935 --> 00:14:52,104
He managed to marry my daughter.

143
00:14:52,187 --> 00:14:54,231
He's really something.

144
00:14:54,315 --> 00:14:55,691
Pardon?

145
00:14:55,774 --> 00:14:58,402
It's a compliment.
As a lawyer, he should be

146
00:14:58,485 --> 00:15:02,364
good at calculating, being practical,
and taking what he wants.

147
00:15:02,448 --> 00:15:05,242
-What do you--
-I'm saying he's smart

148
00:15:05,326 --> 00:15:06,744
he didn't miss this opportunity.

149
00:15:08,621 --> 00:15:11,290
What do you mean by "this opportunity"?

150
00:15:11,373 --> 00:15:12,541
I'm sure you know.

151
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,585
Right.

152
00:15:14,668 --> 00:15:17,087
Whatever you mean by it,

153
00:15:17,171 --> 00:15:19,632
it's a marriage between our kids.

154
00:15:20,257 --> 00:15:21,425
I know that.

155
00:15:21,508 --> 00:15:25,179
Exactly. I just wanted
to say that it'd be nice,

156
00:15:25,262 --> 00:15:28,015
as their parents, if we could help them

157
00:15:28,766 --> 00:15:31,560
lead a happy marriage. That's all.

158
00:15:31,644 --> 00:15:33,520
If it's their marriage,

159
00:15:33,604 --> 00:15:36,482
it's their business to lead a happy life.

160
00:15:36,565 --> 00:15:38,442
Why should we help?

161
00:15:42,655 --> 00:15:44,490
Who's she to tell me what to do?

162
00:15:50,371 --> 00:15:52,373
Divorce or not,

163
00:15:52,456 --> 00:15:53,874
I'm so worried.

164
00:15:55,334 --> 00:15:58,879
Please live a good life, will you?

165
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:00,881
Shoo!

166
00:16:17,231 --> 00:16:19,358
Don't forget to drink orange juice
in the morning.

167
00:16:19,441 --> 00:16:20,776
That's your hangover cure.

168
00:16:24,446 --> 00:16:26,115
Isn't that too cold?

169
00:16:26,198 --> 00:16:28,200
Want me to make you some tea?

170
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:30,619
Something warm would be better.

171
00:16:30,703 --> 00:16:31,745
I'm good.

172
00:16:33,664 --> 00:16:34,665
Hold on.

173
00:16:53,434 --> 00:16:55,728
Keep yourself presentable.
You're not a kid.

174
00:17:15,164 --> 00:17:16,832
My goodness.

175
00:17:18,292 --> 00:17:20,252
I wondered why my heart was pounding.

176
00:17:22,004 --> 00:17:24,673
It was because I was scared. That's it.

177
00:17:25,466 --> 00:17:27,676
That's why my heart was racing so much.

178
00:17:52,159 --> 00:17:55,245
What do you think?
I'm wearing this to the meeting tonight.

179
00:18:02,711 --> 00:18:03,712
I see.

180
00:18:05,339 --> 00:18:07,341
It's a Hercyna vintage jacket from 1982.

181
00:18:08,926 --> 00:18:11,720
-Is that so?
-There are only two pieces in the world.

182
00:18:11,804 --> 00:18:13,555
CEO Hermann's wife has one,

183
00:18:13,639 --> 00:18:14,973
and the other is this one.

184
00:18:20,312 --> 00:18:21,313
You don't like it?

185
00:18:23,607 --> 00:18:24,608
That's not it.

186
00:18:25,484 --> 00:18:26,485
Well…

187
00:18:32,491 --> 00:18:33,700
It looks fine.

188
00:18:46,922 --> 00:18:48,173
Why does she look pretty?

189
00:18:49,883 --> 00:18:50,884
Why?

190
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:54,471
Why on earth?

191
00:18:57,349 --> 00:18:58,350
What are you doing?

192
00:19:09,486 --> 00:19:10,487
Let's go.

193
00:19:13,991 --> 00:19:15,117
I like your suit.

194
00:19:18,537 --> 00:19:19,538
My suit?

195
00:19:19,621 --> 00:19:21,081
Yes. You look good.

196
00:19:40,642 --> 00:19:42,227
You must be in a good mood.

197
00:19:43,604 --> 00:19:44,646
No, not really.

198
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:46,064
But you were humming.

199
00:19:47,441 --> 00:19:48,901
-Was I?
-Yes.

200
00:19:54,448 --> 00:19:55,866
-When?
-Just now.

201
00:20:02,623 --> 00:20:03,749
Are you excited?

202
00:20:03,832 --> 00:20:06,835
Because she complimented you?
Is that why you were humming?

203
00:20:07,586 --> 00:20:08,962
God, have I gone crazy?

204
00:20:10,297 --> 00:20:13,425
Maybe I have since she hasn't
complimented me in so long, or…

205
00:20:22,726 --> 00:20:25,020
Look at her frown.
She's unhappy with something.

206
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,023
She'll throw a fit soon.

207
00:20:28,106 --> 00:20:33,278
Five, four, three, two, one.

208
00:20:33,362 --> 00:20:36,323
What happened to decorating
the personal shopper room like a gallery?

209
00:20:36,406 --> 00:20:38,825
-Oh, no.
-The artist's reputation and colors

210
00:20:38,909 --> 00:20:41,078
don't suit the interior design!

211
00:20:41,161 --> 00:20:44,957
Yelling and glaring like that,
she looks so mean.

212
00:20:45,749 --> 00:20:48,418
That's why I get scared
and my heart races.

213
00:20:53,298 --> 00:20:55,550
Yes, this is what I was talking about!

214
00:20:56,468 --> 00:20:58,303
What happened? She's excited.

215
00:20:59,012 --> 00:21:00,013
Not bad.

216
00:21:12,401 --> 00:21:14,403
What the… What's wrong with me?

217
00:21:16,154 --> 00:21:17,155
Why did I smile?

218
00:21:18,407 --> 00:21:19,866
Get a grip.

219
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:21,368
Hey, that's dangerous.

220
00:21:21,451 --> 00:21:25,289
You know how actors fall in love for real
while filming romantic scenes together.

221
00:21:25,372 --> 00:21:27,207
Like Hyun Bin and Son Ye-jin.

222
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:28,709
That's not the case.

223
00:21:28,792 --> 00:21:31,336
And yet you bought her shoes?

224
00:21:36,091 --> 00:21:37,467
Goodness.

225
00:21:37,551 --> 00:21:40,595
The whole point of an escalator
is to avoid having to walk up.

226
00:21:41,179 --> 00:21:42,514
She's so impatient.

227
00:21:44,266 --> 00:21:45,267
I can't believe her.

228
00:21:47,144 --> 00:21:48,270
Watch out!

229
00:21:56,611 --> 00:21:58,697
Did someone just yell?

230
00:21:58,780 --> 00:21:59,823
I heard it too.

231
00:21:59,906 --> 00:22:02,159
What kind of lunatic yells like that here?

232
00:22:11,585 --> 00:22:12,586
Sir?

233
00:22:13,170 --> 00:22:14,171
Can I help you?

234
00:22:15,797 --> 00:22:16,882
Well…

235
00:22:18,759 --> 00:22:21,428
Do you have a pair of these in size 240?

236
00:22:22,596 --> 00:22:24,556
That's why you bought the shoes for her?

237
00:22:25,557 --> 00:22:27,768
She hasn't changed her will.
I can't let her

238
00:22:27,851 --> 00:22:29,478
-fall and die.
-Right.

239
00:22:30,103 --> 00:22:31,521
-So that's why?
-Of course.

240
00:22:31,605 --> 00:22:32,773
Even I was surprised

241
00:22:32,856 --> 00:22:35,484
that I was so calculating
and cold-hearted.

242
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:37,194
So? What did she say?

243
00:22:50,957 --> 00:22:53,835
So, you bought them
because they were 50% off?

244
00:22:53,919 --> 00:22:55,712
And today is the last day.

245
00:22:55,796 --> 00:22:58,215
Plus, 240 is a popular size,

246
00:22:58,298 --> 00:23:00,717
and the white ones
are sold out all over the country.

247
00:23:00,801 --> 00:23:02,386
Except for this pair.

248
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:04,721
I had to buy them.

249
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:06,681
I'm sure you did.

250
00:23:07,766 --> 00:23:10,060
But my shoe closet

251
00:23:10,143 --> 00:23:13,647
is full of expensive shoes
that I had to pay extra to buy.

252
00:23:13,730 --> 00:23:17,526
Would I ever wear ones
bought at half price?

253
00:23:17,609 --> 00:23:21,279
Of course, I know that you have
a lot of expensive, luxurious shoes.

254
00:23:22,739 --> 00:23:24,282
But none of them are comfy.

255
00:23:26,785 --> 00:23:28,954
-They're pretty.
-You're pretty even without them.

256
00:23:30,288 --> 00:23:35,127
Besides, the heels are so thin and high.

257
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,338
I'm worried you might fall.

258
00:23:40,465 --> 00:23:41,591
So why don't you

259
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,136
wear comfy shoes once in a while?

260
00:23:48,557 --> 00:23:49,641
Leave them here, then.

261
00:23:50,851 --> 00:23:52,519
She didn't like them then.

262
00:23:52,602 --> 00:23:54,813
I couldn't believe her reaction.

263
00:23:54,896 --> 00:23:56,189
But even more unbelievable?

264
00:23:56,273 --> 00:23:57,107
What is it?

265
00:24:00,026 --> 00:24:01,403
She wore them.

266
00:24:10,245 --> 00:24:12,747
-Wow, Ms. Hong looks so…
-Right?

267
00:24:13,373 --> 00:24:14,374
Pretty, right?

268
00:24:15,417 --> 00:24:17,294
No, she looks so feisty today.

269
00:24:20,297 --> 00:24:22,299
As if she's ready to crush anyone.

270
00:24:25,010 --> 00:24:26,011
Exactly.

271
00:24:27,512 --> 00:24:30,515
Anyway, those two meet
so often these days.

272
00:24:31,349 --> 00:24:33,143
-This is Secretary Na.
-Oh, hi.

273
00:24:33,935 --> 00:24:35,061
Right.

274
00:24:35,937 --> 00:24:38,398
It's because of the Hercyna store.

275
00:24:39,983 --> 00:24:42,986
Recently, Mr. Yoon
has been visiting every day,

276
00:24:43,069 --> 00:24:44,488
having meals and coffee,

277
00:24:44,571 --> 00:24:46,531
and even taking walks with her.

278
00:24:48,825 --> 00:24:51,286
It seems you don't know this,

279
00:24:51,369 --> 00:24:53,288
but workaholics even use

280
00:24:53,371 --> 00:24:56,458
mealtimes and coffee breaks
to talk about work.

281
00:24:57,292 --> 00:24:58,126
That's why.

282
00:25:08,261 --> 00:25:09,971
Mr. Yoon may be her friend,

283
00:25:10,055 --> 00:25:12,807
but he clearly doesn't know Hae-in well.

284
00:25:13,683 --> 00:25:14,768
Hae-in hates it

285
00:25:14,851 --> 00:25:18,021
when someone touches her hair like that.

286
00:25:18,647 --> 00:25:19,648
She's smiling.

287
00:25:21,316 --> 00:25:24,152
It seems she doesn't really hate it.

288
00:25:26,404 --> 00:25:29,115
So is it bothering you?
Does it make you jealous?

289
00:25:30,408 --> 00:25:33,411
Were you even listening?
Don't you get my point?

290
00:25:33,495 --> 00:25:35,622
That's your point. You're jealous.

291
00:25:36,831 --> 00:25:38,375
Don't you know what "jealousy" means?

292
00:25:39,167 --> 00:25:41,795
That's what you feel when you like someone

293
00:25:41,878 --> 00:25:44,589
and a rival happens to show up.

294
00:25:44,673 --> 00:25:45,966
That's the wrong premise.

295
00:25:46,049 --> 00:25:48,468
I don't even like Hae-in.
Why would I be jealous?

296
00:25:48,552 --> 00:25:51,263
-So it doesn't bother you?
-No, not at all.

297
00:25:51,346 --> 00:25:53,640
I don't care if they're close

298
00:25:53,723 --> 00:25:55,767
or if they go anywhere together.

299
00:25:55,850 --> 00:25:58,853
I got it, but what are you grilling
instead of meat?

300
00:26:13,118 --> 00:26:14,578
Are you wearing those?

301
00:26:15,495 --> 00:26:19,082
My husband bought them for me
and asked that I wear them. What can I do?

302
00:26:20,375 --> 00:26:24,879
Still, we're meeting the CEO of Hercyna.
Wouldn't it be better to wear their shoes?

303
00:26:24,963 --> 00:26:26,214
Want me to find you some?

304
00:26:27,299 --> 00:26:29,009
I'm wearing their clothes.

305
00:26:29,092 --> 00:26:30,802
Their shoes are uncomfortable.

306
00:26:30,885 --> 00:26:33,972
And he's worried that I might fall.

307
00:26:34,055 --> 00:26:34,889
Who is?

308
00:26:36,016 --> 00:26:36,975
Hyun-woo is.

309
00:26:38,310 --> 00:26:39,811
What a worrywart.

310
00:26:59,289 --> 00:27:00,165
Right.

311
00:27:03,209 --> 00:27:04,252
What?

312
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:08,256
Whatever Hermann says, just listen.

313
00:27:08,882 --> 00:27:09,799
When he's done,

314
00:27:10,675 --> 00:27:11,843
just say one thing.

315
00:27:37,327 --> 00:27:38,662
Sara Lopez?

316
00:27:38,745 --> 00:27:42,082
She's a popular designer in Europe.
We're planning to open up a store.

317
00:27:42,165 --> 00:27:43,041
What about her?

318
00:27:44,668 --> 00:27:46,086
She's Hermann's new mistress.

319
00:27:47,712 --> 00:27:49,005
I see.

320
00:27:49,756 --> 00:27:51,341
And his wife doesn't know?

321
00:27:52,801 --> 00:27:55,679
She's a hot-tempered, competent lawyer.

322
00:27:56,304 --> 00:27:57,263
If she finds out,

323
00:27:57,889 --> 00:28:00,392
he'll never see his baby girl.

324
00:28:44,102 --> 00:28:46,146
Hermann was glaring at you.

325
00:28:48,106 --> 00:28:50,900
Because besides the two,
I was the only one who knew.

326
00:28:52,235 --> 00:28:53,611
Aren't you in a fix, then?

327
00:28:55,071 --> 00:28:56,197
It's all right.

328
00:28:56,281 --> 00:28:59,743
I have a few more cards
to play against him.

329
00:29:02,454 --> 00:29:04,080
Ye-na was right.

330
00:29:04,164 --> 00:29:06,207
You're not the Eun-sung I knew.

331
00:29:06,833 --> 00:29:08,251
What's happened?

332
00:29:10,545 --> 00:29:12,046
I've worked very hard

333
00:29:12,881 --> 00:29:14,466
to hear this from you.

334
00:29:16,092 --> 00:29:19,512
A debt or kindness, I always repay it.
I owe you one.

335
00:29:22,348 --> 00:29:24,058
All right. I'll hold you to it.

336
00:29:31,649 --> 00:29:33,860
WALNUT AND PEANUT SNACKS

337
00:29:37,447 --> 00:29:38,990
One bag of peanut cakes, please.

338
00:29:39,073 --> 00:29:40,116
Sure.

339
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:42,202
Please pack it in two layers.

340
00:29:42,285 --> 00:29:43,286
Okay.

341
00:29:44,829 --> 00:29:46,331
-You're bringing it home?
-Yes.

342
00:29:51,836 --> 00:29:53,630
This is why I'm suspicious.

343
00:29:53,713 --> 00:29:57,717
In my eyes, if you think of her
when you see these snacks

344
00:29:57,801 --> 00:29:59,302
when you're drunk,

345
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,847
it means you love her!

346
00:30:02,931 --> 00:30:03,932
Love, my foot.

347
00:30:04,015 --> 00:30:06,351
-They're just peanut cakes.
-Here.

348
00:30:06,434 --> 00:30:07,519
You want one too?

349
00:30:08,436 --> 00:30:09,896
-Thanks.
-Thank you.

350
00:30:10,563 --> 00:30:11,564
They're just…

351
00:30:14,025 --> 00:30:15,026
peanut cakes.

352
00:30:20,073 --> 00:30:22,742
Where are you? Hurry home.
I have something to tell you.

353
00:30:23,409 --> 00:30:26,037
Don't worry.
It's good news that you'll love.

354
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:27,288
Something to tell me?

355
00:30:27,372 --> 00:30:29,582
Good news that you'll love?

356
00:30:31,918 --> 00:30:33,545
Wait! No way.

357
00:30:33,628 --> 00:30:35,922
-What?
-"I leave all my assets

358
00:30:36,005 --> 00:30:37,799
to Baek Hyun-woo."

359
00:30:37,882 --> 00:30:38,967
Changing her will.

360
00:30:43,179 --> 00:30:45,431
-Come on. No way.
-Yes way!

361
00:30:45,515 --> 00:30:47,684
It must be it! Yay!

362
00:30:47,767 --> 00:30:49,602
Congrats, you punk!

363
00:30:50,311 --> 00:30:52,438
-Don't forget about me.
-It can't be that.

364
00:30:52,522 --> 00:30:53,606
Let go.

365
00:30:53,690 --> 00:30:54,691
You punk!

366
00:30:57,485 --> 00:30:58,403
Hey.

367
00:30:59,237 --> 00:31:00,613
Hey.

368
00:31:03,616 --> 00:31:06,327
These are peanut cakes. Want some?

369
00:31:17,255 --> 00:31:19,257
I wanted to give you this
before it got cold.

370
00:31:20,008 --> 00:31:21,259
So I rushed home.

371
00:31:26,055 --> 00:31:27,056
How is it?

372
00:31:27,891 --> 00:31:28,933
It's good.

373
00:31:29,017 --> 00:31:30,018
It's still warm.

374
00:31:31,144 --> 00:31:32,145
Right?

375
00:31:36,608 --> 00:31:37,609
By the way,

376
00:31:38,526 --> 00:31:42,113
what is this good news I'll love?

377
00:31:42,196 --> 00:31:43,197
Right.

378
00:31:44,657 --> 00:31:45,783
Why don't you open it?

379
00:31:48,036 --> 00:31:49,037
This?

380
00:31:54,626 --> 00:31:55,710
Open it?

381
00:31:59,047 --> 00:32:00,506
Don't be surprised.

382
00:32:03,551 --> 00:32:04,552
Okay.

383
00:32:05,303 --> 00:32:06,387
I won't.

384
00:32:09,641 --> 00:32:11,059
I got it just earlier.

385
00:32:11,142 --> 00:32:13,978
It's from one of the best cancer centers
in Europe.

386
00:32:14,062 --> 00:32:17,440
On the next pages
are their research papers.

387
00:32:25,156 --> 00:32:26,199
Yes.

388
00:32:26,282 --> 00:32:27,325
That's right.

389
00:32:27,408 --> 00:32:29,953
They think they can cure me.

390
00:32:30,620 --> 00:32:32,080
-What?
-And the chance…

391
00:32:36,834 --> 00:32:37,961
is over 50%.

392
00:32:38,878 --> 00:32:40,046
Over?

393
00:32:41,631 --> 00:32:43,299
I knew you'd be so happy.

394
00:32:47,136 --> 00:32:48,137
Here.

395
00:32:49,305 --> 00:32:51,474
The chance is about 51%.

396
00:32:52,350 --> 00:32:54,936
And they'd like
to do clinical treatments on me.

397
00:32:55,019 --> 00:32:57,188
-It's true.
-What did I say?

398
00:32:57,271 --> 00:32:59,273
I said I'd never lose to that illness.

399
00:32:59,941 --> 00:33:01,192
That God's on my side.

400
00:33:01,943 --> 00:33:03,820
You're on my side,

401
00:33:04,654 --> 00:33:05,863
and so is God.

402
00:33:06,948 --> 00:33:08,825
My goodness.

403
00:33:10,076 --> 00:33:11,452
I feel so reassured.

404
00:33:47,739 --> 00:33:48,614
If

405
00:33:49,532 --> 00:33:50,867
she is cured,

406
00:33:52,243 --> 00:33:53,286
then…

407
00:33:53,911 --> 00:33:55,163
The team dinner finished

408
00:33:55,246 --> 00:33:59,000
-at 9:30 p.m. last night, so why…
-Why did you have to bring it up at…

409
00:33:59,083 --> 00:34:00,334
Didn't I tell you?

410
00:34:01,169 --> 00:34:02,754
I'm just worried.

411
00:34:03,671 --> 00:34:05,256
-Say something!
-It's not Hyun-woo.

412
00:34:05,339 --> 00:34:08,009
-You're a part of our Hong family!
-Hyun-woo!

413
00:34:11,095 --> 00:34:14,682
Hurry up. We're going to be late.
This is why you're always late.

414
00:34:15,516 --> 00:34:18,061
-I'm sorry.
-You're so frustrating.

415
00:35:02,188 --> 00:35:03,272
A life like that

416
00:35:04,482 --> 00:35:05,900
for 50 more years?

417
00:35:08,528 --> 00:35:09,529
No.

418
00:35:11,489 --> 00:35:12,657
I should get a divorce

419
00:35:13,449 --> 00:35:15,201
as I originally planned.

420
00:35:17,411 --> 00:35:18,329
DIVORCE AGREEMENT

421
00:35:20,248 --> 00:35:21,374
Right.

422
00:35:22,125 --> 00:35:24,460
Now that I've been cured,

423
00:35:25,545 --> 00:35:27,004
you're going to betray me?

424
00:35:27,630 --> 00:35:30,133
You got your life back,

425
00:35:30,216 --> 00:35:32,426
so I want mine back too.

426
00:35:37,098 --> 00:35:38,099
Right.

427
00:35:39,142 --> 00:35:41,310
People can feel that way.

428
00:35:42,103 --> 00:35:43,104
It's understandable.

429
00:35:46,524 --> 00:35:47,567
However…

430
00:35:59,328 --> 00:36:01,205
Not my people.

431
00:36:08,421 --> 00:36:12,592
It might be worse than my imagination.

432
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,976
God, I'm exhausted.

433
00:36:22,059 --> 00:36:23,144
-Goodness.
-Are you okay?

434
00:36:23,227 --> 00:36:24,478
Yes, I'm all right.

435
00:36:24,562 --> 00:36:26,939
Goodness, it's exhausting.

436
00:36:30,276 --> 00:36:31,944
Goodness.

437
00:36:32,028 --> 00:36:33,821
I've gotten a lot better.

438
00:36:33,905 --> 00:36:36,407
Dad, aren't you thirsty? Have this.

439
00:36:38,284 --> 00:36:39,452
Right. Thanks.

440
00:36:41,579 --> 00:36:44,415
Can I really drink this?
You didn't poison it, did you?

441
00:36:44,498 --> 00:36:46,876
Come on, Dad. Just drink it.

442
00:36:47,627 --> 00:36:49,420
What's gotten into you?

443
00:36:49,503 --> 00:36:51,088
I was always like this.

444
00:36:52,632 --> 00:36:53,716
Look at this.

445
00:36:54,383 --> 00:36:56,052
We used to be so happy together.

446
00:36:56,135 --> 00:36:59,972
I mean, we used to be,
before some bitch entered the picture.

447
00:37:00,056 --> 00:37:01,891
We weren't this messed up.

448
00:37:01,974 --> 00:37:03,976
Mr. Hong, I'll go inside first.

449
00:37:16,155 --> 00:37:18,366
Dad, do you remember

450
00:37:19,116 --> 00:37:21,535
how much you adored me?

451
00:37:21,619 --> 00:37:22,620
You doted on me.

452
00:37:22,703 --> 00:37:26,582
You always bought a gift for me
on your way back from your business trips.

453
00:37:26,666 --> 00:37:28,542
That was ages ago.

454
00:37:28,626 --> 00:37:32,880
You always told me to live
with you forever without getting married.

455
00:37:32,964 --> 00:37:35,341
And see? I'm still by your side.

456
00:37:35,424 --> 00:37:38,719
I didn't tell you
to get married and come back.

457
00:37:38,803 --> 00:37:39,679
Come on.

458
00:37:39,762 --> 00:37:41,931
Love is about coming back, Dad.

459
00:37:42,014 --> 00:37:45,101
Why did I come back within three years
whenever I got married?

460
00:37:45,184 --> 00:37:47,144
That's because

461
00:37:48,062 --> 00:37:50,648
your lovely daughter loves you.

462
00:37:50,731 --> 00:37:52,900
Hey, stop. I'm eating soon.

463
00:37:52,984 --> 00:37:54,777
-I'll lose my appetite.
-Oh, no.

464
00:37:54,860 --> 00:37:57,029
You shouldn't lose your appetite.

465
00:37:57,113 --> 00:38:00,283
At your age, it's more dangerous
than running out of money.

466
00:38:00,366 --> 00:38:03,577
What is it? Just say it.
Why are you being like this?

467
00:38:05,121 --> 00:38:07,873
You know, it's my birthday
the day after tomorrow.

468
00:38:07,957 --> 00:38:09,792
I don't want anything else.

469
00:38:10,584 --> 00:38:14,505
I just want to go on a date
with my beloved dad, just the two of us.

470
00:38:14,588 --> 00:38:15,881
-Please?
-My God.

471
00:38:16,924 --> 00:38:18,759
Please, Dad?

472
00:38:19,635 --> 00:38:21,971
I want to have
something delicious with you.

473
00:38:22,054 --> 00:38:24,598
-Stop it.
-Will you treat me to something nice?

474
00:38:24,682 --> 00:38:27,143
Hey, stop. That's gross!

475
00:38:27,226 --> 00:38:28,477
Stop! Go away!

476
00:38:55,212 --> 00:38:56,297
Hey.

477
00:38:57,757 --> 00:38:59,342
-Hello.
-Hello.

478
00:38:59,425 --> 00:39:02,345
What are you doing here
in the morning on a weekend?

479
00:39:02,428 --> 00:39:04,138
For the negotiation with Hercyna.

480
00:39:04,221 --> 00:39:06,015
Oh, then I should join you.

481
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:10,019
The Legal Team should be in the loop
to work on the details.

482
00:39:10,644 --> 00:39:11,604
That'll come later.

483
00:39:11,687 --> 00:39:15,107
We're discussing the negotiation
between the CEOs

484
00:39:15,191 --> 00:39:17,693
to get rid of any deal-breaking factors.

485
00:39:19,695 --> 00:39:22,198
Are we bothering you?
We can go somewhere else.

486
00:39:22,281 --> 00:39:23,449
What about my hotel?

487
00:39:24,492 --> 00:39:25,576
You can just do it here.

488
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:27,453
Here, comfortably.

489
00:39:29,789 --> 00:39:30,664
Thank you.

490
00:39:31,415 --> 00:39:32,833
I should thank you.

491
00:39:32,917 --> 00:39:34,502
You're helping my wife.

492
00:39:35,169 --> 00:39:36,087
Want some coffee?

493
00:39:36,170 --> 00:39:37,505
-Yes, thanks.
-Sure.

494
00:39:38,798 --> 00:39:41,717
You too? You don't drink coffee
on an empty stomach.

495
00:39:48,766 --> 00:39:49,767
That's true.

496
00:39:51,435 --> 00:39:54,271
-An espresso for you, right?
-Yes.

497
00:40:06,158 --> 00:40:08,577
She cares for me so much.

498
00:40:09,995 --> 00:40:11,122
What?

499
00:40:12,415 --> 00:40:15,918
She says coffee's like poison
on an empty stomach and it's unhealthy.

500
00:40:17,878 --> 00:40:19,463
She doesn't let me drink it.

501
00:40:20,089 --> 00:40:21,799
I mean, I'm not her kid, you know?

502
00:40:23,884 --> 00:40:25,428
I guess she can't stop

503
00:40:26,178 --> 00:40:28,180
worrying about me.

504
00:40:28,264 --> 00:40:30,558
Hae-in must care so much for you.

505
00:40:31,725 --> 00:40:32,726
I envy you.

506
00:40:33,769 --> 00:40:35,271
Well, yes. I think so too.

507
00:40:35,896 --> 00:40:37,231
She's not like that to me.

508
00:40:37,898 --> 00:40:41,819
She always asks me for help,
saying I'm the only one who can help her.

509
00:40:42,570 --> 00:40:43,904
She was always like that.

510
00:40:44,655 --> 00:40:49,285
She'd call me anytime asking for help,
saying I was the only one she had.

511
00:40:49,368 --> 00:40:50,953
How could I not help then?

512
00:40:51,036 --> 00:40:55,082
Even this time around. This kind
of negotiation could even take a year.

513
00:40:55,166 --> 00:40:57,501
But she asked me
to finish it in two weeks.

514
00:40:58,919 --> 00:41:01,797
I won't have time to do anything else
while I'm in Korea.

515
00:41:02,631 --> 00:41:03,674
It seems

516
00:41:03,757 --> 00:41:06,135
I have to be stuck with her all the time.

517
00:41:09,889 --> 00:41:10,890
That's

518
00:41:12,475 --> 00:41:13,726
reassuring.

519
00:41:22,776 --> 00:41:24,862
Are you bringing this to him?

520
00:41:30,910 --> 00:41:32,328
I'm suddenly curious.

521
00:41:33,954 --> 00:41:34,955
About what?

522
00:41:35,039 --> 00:41:38,125
Don't you hate it
when someone touches your hair?

523
00:41:38,834 --> 00:41:40,002
-What?
-I mean,

524
00:41:40,085 --> 00:41:41,587
when I touched it last time,

525
00:41:41,670 --> 00:41:44,507
you yelled at me,
saying I was ruining your hairstyle.

526
00:41:45,549 --> 00:41:46,800
What are you saying?

527
00:41:47,635 --> 00:41:48,469
Put it simply.

528
00:41:50,387 --> 00:41:52,139
You got mad when I did it,

529
00:41:53,140 --> 00:41:55,142
so why didn't you when Mr. Yoon did it?

530
00:41:56,268 --> 00:41:57,102
What?

531
00:42:00,272 --> 00:42:02,358
Oh, that's because--

532
00:42:02,441 --> 00:42:03,651
I want you to be fair.

533
00:42:04,693 --> 00:42:06,320
Not just Mr. Yoon.

534
00:42:06,403 --> 00:42:08,531
If any guy touches your hair,

535
00:42:09,448 --> 00:42:10,449
you should get mad.

536
00:42:12,952 --> 00:42:14,328
Except for your hairdresser.

537
00:42:30,678 --> 00:42:31,679
She just left…

538
00:42:34,056 --> 00:42:35,266
without saying anything.

539
00:42:47,736 --> 00:42:49,280
How could she do that?

540
00:42:49,363 --> 00:42:50,322
Darn it.

541
00:42:54,868 --> 00:42:56,036
Goodness.

542
00:43:01,333 --> 00:43:02,334
God…

543
00:43:04,044 --> 00:43:05,588
This is unbelievable.

544
00:43:06,297 --> 00:43:10,676
I've never been this annoyed
at someone's smile.

545
00:43:10,759 --> 00:43:12,303
He really is something.

546
00:43:23,105 --> 00:43:25,274
He's still smiling. What?

547
00:43:26,692 --> 00:43:29,737
That jerk. Why is he pulling it down?
Hey, you bastard. Wait.

548
00:43:31,614 --> 00:43:33,616
Wait. Hey.

549
00:43:34,491 --> 00:43:36,577
What's wrong with him?

550
00:43:36,660 --> 00:43:39,079
You think I can't watch you
if you do this?

551
00:43:39,163 --> 00:43:41,373
I'll find a way, no matter what.

552
00:44:00,434 --> 00:44:01,435
I'm…

553
00:44:02,436 --> 00:44:04,271
just walking by.

554
00:44:05,606 --> 00:44:06,607
Walking around.

555
00:44:08,692 --> 00:44:11,904
It's not because I'm curious.

556
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:17,284
Goodness.

557
00:44:18,702 --> 00:44:19,703
What?

558
00:44:20,996 --> 00:44:22,206
What is it?

559
00:44:25,042 --> 00:44:27,419
Didn't you say "Honey"?

560
00:44:27,503 --> 00:44:28,754
No, I didn't.

561
00:44:29,380 --> 00:44:30,464
I see.

562
00:44:31,382 --> 00:44:32,549
I must've heard wrong.

563
00:44:32,633 --> 00:44:33,676
All right.

564
00:44:34,301 --> 00:44:36,470
Well, carry on.

565
00:44:37,846 --> 00:44:39,515
Call me if you need me.

566
00:44:39,598 --> 00:44:40,766
No, I won't need you today.

567
00:44:41,558 --> 00:44:42,559
Just go and rest.

568
00:44:44,186 --> 00:44:45,145
I am resting.

569
00:44:46,980 --> 00:44:48,732
-Hey.
-Yes?

570
00:44:48,816 --> 00:44:49,900
No, not you.

571
00:44:49,983 --> 00:44:51,110
Eun-sung!

572
00:44:51,193 --> 00:44:54,530
I heard my sister
was bothering you on Sunday, so I came.

573
00:44:54,613 --> 00:44:56,031
Hey, get lost.

574
00:44:56,490 --> 00:44:57,741
We're working.

575
00:44:57,825 --> 00:45:00,703
You know,
I tried to contact you many times,

576
00:45:00,786 --> 00:45:01,954
but your secretary

577
00:45:02,037 --> 00:45:04,790
doesn't suit your international,
clean-cut image.

578
00:45:04,873 --> 00:45:09,712
She hung up on me without knowing
how close we are. I was so hurt.

579
00:45:09,795 --> 00:45:11,880
Really? I'll talk to them, Mr. Hong.

580
00:45:12,631 --> 00:45:16,176
Don't be so formal with me.
Just treat me like your little brother.

581
00:45:16,260 --> 00:45:19,555
Seriously, I feel closer to you
than Hyun-woo,

582
00:45:19,638 --> 00:45:22,099
who's been my brother-in-law
for three years.

583
00:45:23,225 --> 00:45:24,435
You're still here?

584
00:45:26,478 --> 00:45:27,479
I'm leaving.

585
00:45:28,147 --> 00:45:29,523
-No, don't come out.
-Right.

586
00:45:30,107 --> 00:45:31,108
I won't.

587
00:45:32,025 --> 00:45:33,527
Have you eaten yet?

588
00:45:34,862 --> 00:45:36,280
Why are you so down?

589
00:45:37,030 --> 00:45:41,910
The way I see it,
Eun-sung's like your new hope.

590
00:45:41,994 --> 00:45:43,328
What do you mean?

591
00:45:43,412 --> 00:45:46,582
Hae-in has a 51% chance of living now.

592
00:45:46,665 --> 00:45:49,084
Of course, you should be happy for her.

593
00:45:49,168 --> 00:45:51,670
But your hope is gone.

594
00:45:51,754 --> 00:45:55,340
Your hope for a rich and safe parting.

595
00:45:55,424 --> 00:45:56,425
So?

596
00:45:57,509 --> 00:46:01,930
What if Eun-sung and Hae-in fall in love?

597
00:46:02,014 --> 00:46:03,015
You'll get alimony.

598
00:46:03,098 --> 00:46:04,349
No, not Yoon Eun-sung.

599
00:46:04,433 --> 00:46:05,642
Why not?

600
00:46:05,726 --> 00:46:08,687
That guy's creepy.

601
00:46:12,649 --> 00:46:14,234
Who cares?

602
00:46:14,318 --> 00:46:17,029
Hey, I think he's your savior.

603
00:46:17,112 --> 00:46:20,324
You should be grateful
that he's come to save you.

604
00:46:20,407 --> 00:46:23,619
There is something off with him.

605
00:46:24,703 --> 00:46:27,623
-I can feel it.
-Come on.

606
00:46:29,208 --> 00:46:31,877
Who cares what your savior is like?

607
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:35,297
If you're drowning, and you don't like
the rescuer, will you not

608
00:46:37,049 --> 00:46:38,383
grab the rope?

609
00:46:41,470 --> 00:46:43,806
In any case,
I can't let it be that bastard.

610
00:46:44,765 --> 00:46:45,682
I said no.

611
00:46:50,229 --> 00:46:51,188
Are you okay?

612
00:46:51,271 --> 00:46:52,481
Eun-sung.

613
00:46:53,357 --> 00:46:55,609
See this land? It's a million pyeong.

614
00:46:55,692 --> 00:46:58,737
Neverland is 430,000 pyeong,
and Souland is 280,000 pyeong.

615
00:46:58,821 --> 00:47:00,531
It's bigger than the two combined.

616
00:47:00,614 --> 00:47:01,907
Impressive.

617
00:47:03,075 --> 00:47:05,953
You know the two most important things
in the resort business,

618
00:47:06,036 --> 00:47:07,871
securing the land and licensing.

619
00:47:07,955 --> 00:47:11,333
As you can see, we have the land,
and as for licensing…

620
00:47:13,961 --> 00:47:16,046
We have our person
in the Ministry of Land.

621
00:47:17,589 --> 00:47:18,590
Is that so?

622
00:47:19,299 --> 00:47:21,426
He studied with Queens scholarships.

623
00:47:21,510 --> 00:47:22,678
And he was my tutor.

624
00:47:23,387 --> 00:47:24,763
-I see.
-Right.

625
00:47:25,430 --> 00:47:28,892
K-pop, K-drama.
Korean content is so popular these days.

626
00:47:28,976 --> 00:47:31,436
Let's outdo Disney together, Eun-sung!

627
00:47:34,690 --> 00:47:35,941
I'll think about it.

628
00:48:00,883 --> 00:48:01,717
Oh, my.

629
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:04,177
He meets all these people?

630
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:08,015
Do you know Robert Bailey,
the legendary hedge fund manager?

631
00:48:08,098 --> 00:48:10,767
Among his 12 apprentices,
this guy's the best one.

632
00:48:11,268 --> 00:48:15,606
Robert even entrusted his asset management
with him. What more is there to say?

633
00:48:16,982 --> 00:48:17,983
Really?

634
00:48:18,108 --> 00:48:20,819
He's perfect
as Mr. Hong Soo-cheol's partner.

635
00:48:22,404 --> 00:48:25,198
But he's quite picky, so…

636
00:48:26,283 --> 00:48:29,161
But he's willingly
helping Hae-in regarding Hercyna.

637
00:48:29,244 --> 00:48:31,455
Yes, since the two are so close.

638
00:48:32,915 --> 00:48:37,753
And that might be why
Mr. Yoon isn't getting close to Mr. Hong.

639
00:48:39,004 --> 00:48:40,255
What do you mean?

640
00:48:40,339 --> 00:48:41,298
Think about it.

641
00:48:41,381 --> 00:48:42,549
For Ms. Hong,

642
00:48:42,633 --> 00:48:46,720
if Hercyna opens in her mall, she'll reach
one trillion won in sales for sure.

643
00:48:46,803 --> 00:48:51,683
Then the chairman will lean towards
giving the group to her, as he promised.

644
00:48:51,767 --> 00:48:52,976
Are you saying

645
00:48:53,060 --> 00:48:57,356
Hae-in doesn't want Soo-cheol to succeed
in attracting investment for the resort?

646
00:48:58,315 --> 00:49:01,693
Yes! Soo-cheol could turn the tables.

647
00:49:03,236 --> 00:49:07,658
I mean, I don't know
what Ms. Hong told Mr. Yoon,

648
00:49:07,741 --> 00:49:11,244
but it seems he doesn't consider
Mr. Hong as a potential partner.

649
00:49:12,037 --> 00:49:14,915
He's having dinner
with Chairman Yeom's grandchild tonight.

650
00:49:17,793 --> 00:49:20,212
Fortune telling doesn't lie.

651
00:49:20,712 --> 00:49:21,964
I told you, didn't I?

652
00:49:22,047 --> 00:49:27,010
Ms. Hong's fated
to prey on her siblings all her life.

653
00:49:28,679 --> 00:49:31,974
Anyway, you don't need anything else
to deal with her.

654
00:49:32,766 --> 00:49:35,185
Fortune telling is like the Bible to her.

655
00:49:35,268 --> 00:49:38,188
If you look up anything online
and tell her,

656
00:49:38,271 --> 00:49:39,606
she just believes it.

657
00:49:39,690 --> 00:49:42,067
But that worked to your advantage.

658
00:49:43,276 --> 00:49:48,240
That's true. I've benefitted
a lot from it for about 15 years.

659
00:50:25,819 --> 00:50:26,945
What brings you here?

660
00:50:30,490 --> 00:50:31,658
I knew it.

661
00:50:32,367 --> 00:50:36,621
If I hadn't withdrawn the suit, your mall
in Gwanggyo wouldn't even be happening.

662
00:50:37,164 --> 00:50:38,165
Do you want that?

663
00:50:41,752 --> 00:50:43,795
Stop beating around the bush.

664
00:50:44,880 --> 00:50:45,881
Just tell me.

665
00:50:47,966 --> 00:50:50,635
What did you tell
Eun-sung about Soo-cheol?

666
00:50:50,719 --> 00:50:54,765
What did you say that made him
not consider investing in Soo-cheol?

667
00:50:54,848 --> 00:50:55,974
What do you mean?

668
00:50:56,058 --> 00:50:57,392
It's obvious.

669
00:50:57,476 --> 00:51:02,355
"If Soo-cheol gets investment, it's bad
for me. So invest in Sang-jin instead."

670
00:51:02,439 --> 00:51:04,816
Because that would make
the chairman furious.

671
00:51:04,900 --> 00:51:07,944
Do you think that even makes sense?

672
00:51:08,695 --> 00:51:11,364
Yes! I think
you're more than capable of doing that.

673
00:51:11,448 --> 00:51:14,284
Because you're a bitch
who's selfish to the bone.

674
00:51:15,035 --> 00:51:19,081
You don't care if anyone around you dies.
You just find a way to save yourself.

675
00:51:19,164 --> 00:51:21,041
And that's why your older brother…

676
00:51:30,842 --> 00:51:33,011
She's been feeling unwell
since this morning.

677
00:51:33,678 --> 00:51:35,097
I think she needs to rest.

678
00:51:35,180 --> 00:51:36,223
I'm sorry, Mother.

679
00:51:37,808 --> 00:51:40,435
So are you telling me to leave?

680
00:51:40,936 --> 00:51:42,771
When I'm still talking to her?

681
00:51:45,649 --> 00:51:46,650
I'm sorry.

682
00:52:24,312 --> 00:52:25,397
Let's tell your family.

683
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:28,275
I said no.

684
00:52:28,358 --> 00:52:31,194
Situations like earlier
can happen anytime.

685
00:52:31,278 --> 00:52:33,155
They might find out.

686
00:52:33,238 --> 00:52:34,489
I'll get treated.

687
00:52:36,408 --> 00:52:38,702
You're acting
like I'll drop dead tomorrow.

688
00:52:38,785 --> 00:52:39,828
You're being

689
00:52:40,745 --> 00:52:42,205
selfish and irresponsible.

690
00:52:43,331 --> 00:52:44,332
Yes.

691
00:52:44,833 --> 00:52:48,670
You're thinking about your money, stocks,
and the One Trillion Club. I get it.

692
00:52:49,588 --> 00:52:54,050
I get that you're worried your family
could take what's yours if they find out.

693
00:52:54,843 --> 00:52:55,844
But,

694
00:52:57,387 --> 00:52:59,389
keeping this important matter from them

695
00:53:00,140 --> 00:53:02,392
because you don't want anything
to be taken.

696
00:53:03,643 --> 00:53:04,477
Is that right?

697
00:53:08,231 --> 00:53:09,691
I don't want to shock them.

698
00:53:12,903 --> 00:53:14,070
My parents…

699
00:53:20,785 --> 00:53:22,746
They already lost a child.

700
00:53:29,961 --> 00:53:31,338
So why scare them?

701
00:53:35,342 --> 00:53:37,344
I can never be a good daughter anyway.

702
00:53:38,345 --> 00:53:39,346
I just

703
00:53:40,513 --> 00:53:43,058
don't want to be
a more terrible existence to my family.

704
00:53:44,517 --> 00:53:45,894
And more importantly,

705
00:53:47,020 --> 00:53:50,607
I'm confident I'll be cured.
So stop treating me like a patient.

706
00:53:58,573 --> 00:53:59,574
Can you leave?

707
00:54:00,200 --> 00:54:01,034
I want to rest.

708
00:54:15,257 --> 00:54:16,424
And the stock purchase?

709
00:54:16,967 --> 00:54:20,720
We bought 14.7% in total, 4.9% per person.

710
00:54:21,846 --> 00:54:23,765
And the directors supporting the chairman?

711
00:54:31,147 --> 00:54:34,484
The rate of return of the last blind trust
was close to 90%,

712
00:54:34,567 --> 00:54:37,779
so they're eager to join the next fund.

713
00:54:37,862 --> 00:54:41,283
We need to lead them to put
Queens stocks up as collateral next.

714
00:54:41,366 --> 00:54:43,159
The minimum amount is so high,

715
00:54:43,243 --> 00:54:46,204
I doubt they can come up
with that much cash in days.

716
00:54:46,288 --> 00:54:48,957
If we rush them,
they'll put their stocks up as collateral.

717
00:54:50,417 --> 00:54:51,876
Next is Chairman Hong.

718
00:54:52,711 --> 00:54:55,005
The prosecution investigation.

719
00:54:56,172 --> 00:54:57,215
I feel bad for him.

720
00:54:57,299 --> 00:54:59,342
He hates jail.

721
00:55:03,221 --> 00:55:05,307
By the way, how will you do it?

722
00:55:06,808 --> 00:55:09,477
The chairman's real safekeeper

723
00:55:10,103 --> 00:55:12,439
is Song Jeong-beom in Finance.

724
00:55:12,522 --> 00:55:17,110
He's siphoning off his own share
as well as the chairman's slush funds.

725
00:55:18,111 --> 00:55:21,031
We'll hand all the evidence
over to the prosecution.

726
00:55:21,114 --> 00:55:23,325
And as they look into the higher-ups,

727
00:55:23,408 --> 00:55:26,328
they will end up investigating
the chairman too.

728
00:55:39,007 --> 00:55:41,468
You can see the Queens Tower from here.

729
00:55:44,429 --> 00:55:45,680
And I like that.

730
00:55:46,848 --> 00:55:50,143
It feels like
I'm looking at a delicious meal.

731
00:56:10,038 --> 00:56:11,039
Damn it.

732
00:56:12,415 --> 00:56:14,584
I told you to make the font bigger.

733
00:56:15,085 --> 00:56:18,755
Darn it. Prepare the documents again
and set another meeting.

734
00:56:18,838 --> 00:56:20,548
I can't believe them.

735
00:56:21,633 --> 00:56:22,550
Get out!

736
00:56:24,135 --> 00:56:25,053
Out!

737
00:56:34,604 --> 00:56:37,107
I think I can let you join
the private equity fund.

738
00:56:37,190 --> 00:56:39,651
The minimum amount is 20 billion won.

739
00:56:39,734 --> 00:56:43,405
And you can put your Queens stocks up
as collateral if you're short of cash.

740
00:56:43,488 --> 00:56:46,574
The earnings rate's expected to be higher.
First come, first served.

741
00:56:46,658 --> 00:56:49,661
So make a quick decision.
Confidentiality is a must.

742
00:56:49,744 --> 00:56:51,287
-Thank you.
-I understand.

743
00:56:51,371 --> 00:56:52,455
That's possible.

744
00:56:56,209 --> 00:56:57,961
She's already here.

745
00:56:58,044 --> 00:57:00,338
What's gotten into Beom-ja?

746
00:57:01,506 --> 00:57:04,384
Why does she suddenly
want to treat me to a meal?

747
00:57:10,598 --> 00:57:12,016
The chairman has arrived.

748
00:57:30,743 --> 00:57:32,245
No, Dad. You can't leave.

749
00:57:32,328 --> 00:57:33,997
-Over my dead body.
-Move.

750
00:57:35,957 --> 00:57:38,001
Dad, just hear me out.

751
00:57:38,084 --> 00:57:39,502
I don't want anything else.

752
00:57:41,337 --> 00:57:42,630
Just give me a chance.

753
00:57:42,714 --> 00:57:43,882
You bastard.

754
00:57:43,965 --> 00:57:45,508
Did I not give you a chance?

755
00:57:46,259 --> 00:57:50,096
I gave you one, but you sold me out
to the prosecution to save yourself!

756
00:57:51,264 --> 00:57:54,476
While I was locked up,
you schemed to take my place

757
00:57:54,559 --> 00:57:57,103
with the directors who supported you.

758
00:57:57,187 --> 00:57:59,606
-Have you forgotten?
-I wasn't in my right mind.

759
00:57:59,689 --> 00:58:04,152
I heard you were trying
to pin the embezzlement charge on me,

760
00:58:04,235 --> 00:58:05,278
so I lost it.

761
00:58:05,361 --> 00:58:07,071
I'm so sorry.

762
00:58:08,781 --> 00:58:10,408
It's been 20 years.

763
00:58:10,492 --> 00:58:12,911
You would've even forgiven a stranger
after this long.

764
00:58:12,994 --> 00:58:14,746
Why are you so harsh on your son?

765
00:58:14,829 --> 00:58:16,998
I would rather forgive a stranger!

766
00:58:17,081 --> 00:58:19,709
How could I forgive my own child
who betrayed me?

767
00:58:21,336 --> 00:58:22,504
I just can't.

768
00:58:23,588 --> 00:58:25,507
So never do something like this again.

769
00:58:25,590 --> 00:58:26,508
Dad!

770
00:58:27,592 --> 00:58:28,885
I missed you.

771
00:58:29,385 --> 00:58:31,095
That's really why I came.

772
00:58:34,974 --> 00:58:36,392
Well, you've seen me now.

773
00:58:38,561 --> 00:58:39,562
I don't want to

774
00:58:40,563 --> 00:58:41,773
see you again.

775
00:58:42,732 --> 00:58:43,858
You ingrate.

776
00:58:44,526 --> 00:58:46,110
Don't even come to my funeral.

777
00:58:49,739 --> 00:58:50,949
Darn it.

778
00:59:10,927 --> 00:59:12,679
Why do you look so down?

779
00:59:13,972 --> 00:59:15,473
It seems you haven't eaten.

780
00:59:19,561 --> 00:59:20,853
When you're not feeling well,

781
00:59:21,688 --> 00:59:23,231
there's nothing better than

782
00:59:23,314 --> 00:59:25,525
a bowl of this.

783
00:59:27,235 --> 00:59:30,863
My mother always made me this
when I was sick.

784
00:59:31,489 --> 00:59:35,868
Back when I used to sell newspapers
and shine people's shoes in Myeong-dong.

785
00:59:35,952 --> 00:59:37,954
When I was hungry or sick,

786
00:59:40,415 --> 00:59:42,959
I always thought of this.

787
00:59:43,751 --> 00:59:44,961
Have some.

788
00:59:46,087 --> 00:59:50,174
From sleeping on the streets
using newspapers as blankets

789
00:59:50,967 --> 00:59:56,723
to owning one of Korea's
top department stores and mart franchises,

790
00:59:56,806 --> 00:59:58,641
it took 60 years.

791
01:00:00,184 --> 01:00:02,729
But why does it feel like

792
01:00:03,646 --> 01:00:05,690
I'm standing alone in the wilderness?

793
01:00:06,357 --> 01:00:08,818
Something must've
hurt your feelings badly.

794
01:00:09,527 --> 01:00:11,571
Only I know how tenderhearted

795
01:00:12,405 --> 01:00:13,656
you are.

796
01:00:27,462 --> 01:00:29,380
It tastes just like

797
01:00:30,506 --> 01:00:32,050
my mother's.

798
01:00:39,474 --> 01:00:41,059
Why can't you give us a refund?

799
01:00:41,142 --> 01:00:43,686
My baby's skin got ruined
after she used this,

800
01:00:43,770 --> 01:00:47,106
but you can't give us a refund,
let alone compensate us?

801
01:00:47,190 --> 01:00:50,401
Sir, it's been over eight months
since you purchased the product,

802
01:00:50,485 --> 01:00:52,612
and you've almost used it all.

803
01:00:52,695 --> 01:00:54,530
Hey. I'm glad you brought it up.

804
01:00:54,614 --> 01:00:57,408
My face looks like this
because I used this much.

805
01:00:57,492 --> 01:01:00,495
If I hadn't, my skin
wouldn't have become like this!

806
01:01:00,578 --> 01:01:03,331
Babe, don't get worked up.
It'll get worse.

807
01:01:04,082 --> 01:01:06,000
Just give us a refund right now.

808
01:01:06,084 --> 01:01:07,877
Sir, we can't do that.

809
01:01:07,960 --> 01:01:09,962
Didn't I make myself clear enough?

810
01:01:14,175 --> 01:01:16,260
Sir, please calm down.

811
01:01:16,344 --> 01:01:18,179
How can I calm down?

812
01:01:19,305 --> 01:01:23,309
Right. You think I'm one
of those obnoxious customers, don't you?

813
01:01:23,393 --> 01:01:25,395
Want me to show you the real thing?

814
01:01:30,358 --> 01:01:32,652
Sir, you can't do this here.

815
01:01:34,237 --> 01:01:38,074
I wanted to use our security deposit
for her surgery, but my mom won't listen.

816
01:01:41,202 --> 01:01:45,039
This is an unreasonable demand.
We cannot help you.

817
01:01:45,123 --> 01:01:46,499
"Unreasonable"?

818
01:01:46,582 --> 01:01:49,752
You're hopeless. Come here.
How dare you talk to me--

819
01:01:54,924 --> 01:01:56,175
Who the hell are you?

820
01:01:57,009 --> 01:01:58,010
Let go.

821
01:01:58,594 --> 01:01:59,887
Let go of me.

822
01:02:03,307 --> 01:02:05,059
This is not the place for such behavior.

823
01:02:05,143 --> 01:02:08,688
Look, I have no business
with you small fry.

824
01:02:08,771 --> 01:02:09,897
Bring your CEO.

825
01:02:09,981 --> 01:02:11,899
Bring your CEO right now!

826
01:02:12,608 --> 01:02:14,193
-She's here.
-What?

827
01:02:14,277 --> 01:02:15,611
I'm the CEO.

828
01:02:17,155 --> 01:02:18,364
Are you the CEO?

829
01:02:18,448 --> 01:02:20,825
Why didn't you
train your employee properly?

830
01:02:20,908 --> 01:02:23,202
You're right.
I don't think I did it properly.

831
01:02:25,997 --> 01:02:27,123
Ms. Kim Min-ji?

832
01:02:28,458 --> 01:02:30,084
Deal with our customers only.

833
01:02:30,168 --> 01:02:33,004
As for criminals, report them
to the police without warning.

834
01:02:33,087 --> 01:02:35,339
What? A criminal?

835
01:02:35,423 --> 01:02:37,759
You call your customers criminals?

836
01:02:37,842 --> 01:02:39,594
Babe, are you filming this?

837
01:02:39,677 --> 01:02:40,845
Yeah.

838
01:02:40,928 --> 01:02:43,639
The CEO of this mall
looks down on her customers.

839
01:02:43,723 --> 01:02:45,933
Let's sue her and teach her a lesson.

840
01:02:46,017 --> 01:02:47,268
Let's do that.

841
01:02:48,603 --> 01:02:50,146
Make sure to do it.

842
01:02:50,229 --> 01:02:51,230
I will too.

843
01:02:52,940 --> 01:02:55,777
I know well
since my husband is a good lawyer.

844
01:02:55,860 --> 01:02:57,028
You can be charged

845
01:02:57,111 --> 01:02:59,989
with obstruction of business,
special assault,

846
01:03:00,072 --> 01:03:01,866
and property damage.

847
01:03:02,450 --> 01:03:06,704
And I'll file another suit
for the sales loss you caused.

848
01:03:07,538 --> 01:03:09,707
-Did you all film it?
-Yes, we did!

849
01:03:09,791 --> 01:03:12,293
-I did. Here!
-Please make way.

850
01:03:14,253 --> 01:03:15,505
Take them to the police.

851
01:03:15,588 --> 01:03:16,964
Let's go, babe.

852
01:03:25,473 --> 01:03:26,849
Thank you.

853
01:03:30,394 --> 01:03:32,772
By the way, Mr. Baek, about Park Seok-hun.

854
01:03:33,606 --> 01:03:35,316
What about him?

855
01:03:35,399 --> 01:03:38,027
He's going around saying

856
01:03:38,110 --> 01:03:43,032
that the Yongdu Pear you're promoting
as our village specialty has no future.

857
01:03:43,115 --> 01:03:45,493
He claims the Yongdu Apple will be

858
01:03:45,576 --> 01:03:47,912
the new K-food craze around the world.

859
01:03:47,995 --> 01:03:49,747
Apple? Goodness.

860
01:03:49,831 --> 01:03:51,290
That's just ridiculous.

861
01:03:51,374 --> 01:03:53,751
Traditionally, apples
are no match for pears.

862
01:03:53,835 --> 01:03:55,461
Of course… Really?

863
01:03:56,087 --> 01:03:59,006
Just think about memorial services.

864
01:03:59,090 --> 01:04:01,551
We put pears on the tables, not apples!

865
01:04:01,634 --> 01:04:05,680
Besides, persimmons and pears go together.
Persimmons and apples don't.

866
01:04:05,763 --> 01:04:09,934
How dare he downplay the importance
of pears, our traditional fruit?

867
01:04:10,017 --> 01:04:12,311
Anyway, this guy's running

868
01:04:12,395 --> 01:04:16,065
an election campaign in such smart ways.

869
01:04:16,148 --> 01:04:18,526
You know his mom's restaurant?

870
01:04:18,609 --> 01:04:23,406
He's offering half-price lunches,
so everyone's eating there now.

871
01:04:23,489 --> 01:04:24,448
You idiot!

872
01:04:24,532 --> 01:04:25,783
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

873
01:04:26,701 --> 01:04:27,827
That little…

874
01:04:28,411 --> 01:04:30,913
He's not playing fair, is he?

875
01:04:30,997 --> 01:04:32,623
Are you going there?

876
01:04:33,791 --> 01:04:35,376
HALF-PRICE LUNCH

877
01:04:42,800 --> 01:04:43,676
Hello.

878
01:04:43,759 --> 01:04:45,136
Hey, Mr. Park.

879
01:04:45,219 --> 01:04:47,096
The soup is especially good today.

880
01:04:47,179 --> 01:04:48,931
Come on. It's always been good.

881
01:04:49,015 --> 01:04:51,642
What is this?

882
01:04:51,726 --> 01:04:53,811
It's like a feast.

883
01:04:53,895 --> 01:04:56,814
We should compete with pledges and plans.

884
01:04:56,898 --> 01:05:00,526
But he's trying to win people over
with a popular song.

885
01:05:00,610 --> 01:05:04,572
I mean, if he wins the election like this,
it's not his victory. It's the singer's!

886
01:05:04,655 --> 01:05:09,201
It should be considered
an election law violation. Yes.

887
01:05:09,285 --> 01:05:11,162
Chun-sik, gather the evidence.

888
01:05:11,245 --> 01:05:15,249
Those who entertain and those
who play along. I'll report the whole lot!

889
01:05:16,167 --> 01:05:17,293
Come on!

890
01:05:21,255 --> 01:05:22,423
You're all doomed.

891
01:05:25,259 --> 01:05:26,552
Wait. What…

892
01:05:27,678 --> 01:05:28,888
-Mr. Baek.
-What?

893
01:05:39,315 --> 01:05:42,693
Seok-hun! I'll have one more pork platter.

894
01:05:42,777 --> 01:05:43,819
One more soju, too!

895
01:05:43,903 --> 01:05:46,405
It's so delicious!

896
01:05:46,489 --> 01:05:48,240
That piece of…

897
01:05:49,033 --> 01:05:50,117
You son of…

898
01:05:50,201 --> 01:05:51,243
I ought to…

899
01:05:51,327 --> 01:05:52,495
How bad is it?

900
01:05:52,578 --> 01:05:55,247
He walked right into their trap.

901
01:05:55,331 --> 01:06:00,002
Family corruption. It's an issue even
the country's presidents couldn't avoid.

902
01:06:00,086 --> 01:06:03,756
The current village head's son let
the opposite side treat him to a meal.

903
01:06:03,839 --> 01:06:07,218
People say the head's family is ruined

904
01:06:07,301 --> 01:06:10,513
because his children
weren't properly disciplined.

905
01:06:10,596 --> 01:06:11,806
You idiot!

906
01:06:11,889 --> 01:06:12,974
I can't believe you!

907
01:06:15,351 --> 01:06:17,603
Dad, I'll change their opinion
from now on.

908
01:06:17,687 --> 01:06:18,854
What can you do?

909
01:06:18,938 --> 01:06:20,940
My salon produces roughly 90%

910
01:06:21,023 --> 01:06:23,651
of the rumors going around Yongdu-ri.

911
01:06:23,734 --> 01:06:25,152
You know, gossipers!

912
01:06:26,070 --> 01:06:28,864
-We can use them.
-Like a smear campaign?

913
01:06:28,948 --> 01:06:32,034
Exactly! Seok-hun stole snacks
from our store

914
01:06:32,118 --> 01:06:33,327
when he was a kid.

915
01:06:33,411 --> 01:06:34,578
We'll expose that.

916
01:06:34,662 --> 01:06:37,748
"He who will steal an egg
will steal an ox!"

917
01:06:38,749 --> 01:06:39,917
What do you think?

918
01:06:41,711 --> 01:06:42,962
Got a cigarette?

919
01:06:43,045 --> 01:06:44,255
I quit smoking.

920
01:07:01,772 --> 01:07:02,940
Mi-seon, are you coming?

921
01:07:03,024 --> 01:07:05,943
Your father and Seok-hun
will have a big face-off.

922
01:07:06,027 --> 01:07:07,319
Go ahead.

923
01:07:07,403 --> 01:07:13,075
I don't think so. Your family needs
as many people as possible on their side.

924
01:07:13,159 --> 01:07:14,744
-Why?
-What do you mean, why?

925
01:07:15,369 --> 01:07:18,205
Because the head is at a disadvantage now.

926
01:07:18,289 --> 01:07:19,790
Just go!

927
01:07:19,874 --> 01:07:20,875
Just come!

928
01:07:20,958 --> 01:07:22,626
For God's sake! Just go!

929
01:07:23,169 --> 01:07:24,211
No, Pinky!

930
01:07:24,670 --> 01:07:26,505
You go back in.

931
01:07:26,589 --> 01:07:29,050
I am standing here

932
01:07:29,133 --> 01:07:31,927
because our village needs young people.

933
01:07:32,011 --> 01:07:33,262
As I said earlier,

934
01:07:33,345 --> 01:07:37,391
I will make the Yongdu Apple
a K-food loved by people around the world!

935
01:07:37,475 --> 01:07:41,771
I, Park Seok-hun, will recover
the two years Yongdu-ri lost!

936
01:07:44,565 --> 01:07:46,108
He's well received.

937
01:07:46,192 --> 01:07:47,193
It's okay.

938
01:07:48,360 --> 01:07:49,612
It's all right.

939
01:07:51,697 --> 01:07:53,699
Everyone, our Yongdu-ri

940
01:07:53,783 --> 01:07:56,786
is like the heart of Korean pears.

941
01:07:56,869 --> 01:08:00,790
Well, isn't the heart of pears
Naju or Seongju?

942
01:08:00,873 --> 01:08:05,461
That's right! Yongdu-ri
isn't the heart. It's more like…

943
01:08:05,544 --> 01:08:06,545
How do I put it?

944
01:08:06,629 --> 01:08:09,340
It's more like the intestine.

945
01:08:09,423 --> 01:08:10,341
Am I right?

946
01:08:11,675 --> 01:08:14,845
Right. If it were the heart, our pears

947
01:08:14,929 --> 01:08:19,016
would be sold
at his daughter-in-law's department store.

948
01:08:19,100 --> 01:08:20,434
You're right!

949
01:08:22,978 --> 01:08:26,273
What? Why bring that up here?

950
01:08:26,357 --> 01:08:27,566
My daughter-in-law

951
01:08:27,650 --> 01:08:30,277
keeps her work and private life apart!

952
01:08:30,361 --> 01:08:32,822
I get that she's a good CEO.

953
01:08:32,905 --> 01:08:33,864
But her private life?

954
01:08:33,948 --> 01:08:37,201
To be blunt, we only heard
she and your son got married.

955
01:08:37,284 --> 01:08:40,830
-We've never seen her.
-Didn't she come on a chopper?

956
01:08:40,913 --> 01:08:43,707
Right. I thought war had broken out then.

957
01:08:43,791 --> 01:08:46,710
It's true that she's never visited
since they got married.

958
01:08:46,794 --> 01:08:48,504
It was before they got married?

959
01:08:50,840 --> 01:08:52,508
-What?
-What's going on?

960
01:08:52,591 --> 01:08:55,219
-Is it an earthquake?
-What's happening?

961
01:08:56,303 --> 01:08:57,763
YONGDU-RI COMMUNITY HALL

962
01:09:04,603 --> 01:09:06,939
-What's that?
-Film it.

963
01:09:08,023 --> 01:09:09,608
They brought a lot.

964
01:09:40,097 --> 01:09:41,265
Father?

965
01:09:43,434 --> 01:09:44,768
Oh, my God.

966
01:09:44,852 --> 01:09:46,061
Oh, my.

967
01:09:56,530 --> 01:09:57,489
No way…

968
01:10:00,409 --> 01:10:01,660
She came.

969
01:10:01,744 --> 01:10:02,953
Finally.

970
01:10:10,419 --> 01:10:13,964
What are you doing here?

971
01:10:14,048 --> 01:10:15,549
I'm glad you're all here.

972
01:10:16,091 --> 01:10:18,219
I missed your last birthday,

973
01:10:18,302 --> 01:10:21,972
so I came to treat
the villagers to a meal.

974
01:10:25,476 --> 01:10:29,688
Hello, I'm Hong Hae-in,
the village head's daughter-in-law.

975
01:10:34,151 --> 01:10:35,361
What's going on?

976
01:10:35,444 --> 01:10:36,946
I texted her.

977
01:10:37,029 --> 01:10:40,241
You said you'd visit us one of these days.

978
01:10:40,324 --> 01:10:44,328
Can that day be today and right now?

979
01:10:44,411 --> 01:10:48,707
My father's running for reelection,
and it's not looking good.

980
01:10:48,791 --> 01:10:52,878
I think he needs to show people
someone influential is supporting him.

981
01:11:01,178 --> 01:11:02,513
Oh, she read it!

982
01:11:02,596 --> 01:11:03,597
It says "read."

983
01:11:08,060 --> 01:11:09,561
She came because of that text?

984
01:11:10,312 --> 01:11:11,480
I can't believe it either.

985
01:11:12,898 --> 01:11:14,692
Good job!

986
01:11:16,110 --> 01:11:17,361
Hong Hae-in!

987
01:11:17,444 --> 01:11:18,737
It's not much.

988
01:11:18,821 --> 01:11:21,949
Expensive nutritional supplements,
ginseng,

989
01:11:22,032 --> 01:11:25,160
cosmetics, silk scarves,
cashmere mufflers,

990
01:11:25,244 --> 01:11:26,954
Italian leather gloves, so on.

991
01:11:27,538 --> 01:11:30,207
I was going to buy
just a little for Father,

992
01:11:30,291 --> 01:11:31,417
but I went overboard.

993
01:11:31,500 --> 01:11:32,793
You can share.

994
01:11:33,377 --> 01:11:36,005
Oh, my. I can't believe you.

995
01:11:36,088 --> 01:11:38,590
You bought too much.

996
01:11:41,176 --> 01:11:44,054
-Baek Du-gwan!
-Baek Du-gwan!

997
01:11:44,138 --> 01:11:48,976
-Hae-in!
-Baek Du-gwan!

998
01:11:49,059 --> 01:11:52,229
Everyone! What's Yongdu-ri's specialty?
Apples or pears?

999
01:11:52,313 --> 01:11:53,897
-Pears!
-Pears!

1000
01:11:55,607 --> 01:11:58,610
-Baek Du-gwan!
-Baek Du-gwan!

1001
01:11:58,694 --> 01:12:01,030
-Hae-in!
-Baek Du-gwan!

1002
01:12:01,113 --> 01:12:03,365
BAEK DU-GWAN
A HARD WORKER WHO PROTECTS YONGDU-RI

1003
01:12:32,728 --> 01:12:35,481
Hyun-woo. Hae-in's here.

1004
01:12:39,485 --> 01:12:41,528
-Hey.
-Mom, I missed your call.

1005
01:12:41,612 --> 01:12:43,739
It's all right. How are you?

1006
01:12:43,822 --> 01:12:47,534
I heard Mi-seon and Hyeon-tae went there.
You must've been surprised.

1007
01:12:47,618 --> 01:12:51,121
No, it's okay.
Nothing bad happened, so don't worry.

1008
01:12:51,205 --> 01:12:52,414
And Hae-in is…

1009
01:12:52,498 --> 01:12:53,916
Yes, she's doing well too.

1010
01:12:54,583 --> 01:12:55,459
What do you mean?

1011
01:12:55,542 --> 01:12:56,877
Did you two fight?

1012
01:12:58,962 --> 01:12:59,880
Of course not.

1013
01:12:59,963 --> 01:13:02,633
Then why don't you know where she is?

1014
01:13:02,716 --> 01:13:04,593
She's here.

1015
01:13:04,676 --> 01:13:06,678
What? Why would she be there?

1016
01:13:06,762 --> 01:13:08,430
You should come ask her yourself.

1017
01:13:08,514 --> 01:13:11,225
The whole village
is having a feast thanks to her.

1018
01:13:13,310 --> 01:13:14,645
What's she talking about?

1019
01:13:17,272 --> 01:13:18,941
Where's Hae-in right now?

1020
01:13:46,385 --> 01:13:48,512
BAEK HYUN-WOO

1021
01:15:10,636 --> 01:15:11,845
Who are you?

1022
01:15:13,305 --> 01:15:14,264
Me?

1023
01:15:15,182 --> 01:15:16,433
I'm the daughter-in-law.

1024
01:15:17,059 --> 01:15:19,353
-Who are you?
-I know everyone in this family,

1025
01:15:19,436 --> 01:15:20,646
but I've never seen you.

1026
01:15:22,731 --> 01:15:23,815
I don't come here often.

1027
01:15:29,905 --> 01:15:32,491
Why are you looking at me like that?
I'm part of the family.

1028
01:15:32,574 --> 01:15:33,867
Then what's the dog's name?

1029
01:15:37,329 --> 01:15:38,539
Musty.

1030
01:15:38,622 --> 01:15:39,540
Spotty?

1031
01:15:39,623 --> 01:15:40,582
They have no dog.

1032
01:15:41,291 --> 01:15:42,417
You look suspicious.

1033
01:15:42,501 --> 01:15:44,545
Why are you so suspicious?

1034
01:15:44,628 --> 01:15:48,131
I'm the wife of Baek Hyun-woo,
the son of this family. Happy? Now go.

1035
01:15:48,215 --> 01:15:51,218
You're the building owner.
You should've told me sooner.

1036
01:15:51,301 --> 01:15:53,262
-What?
-My dad told me

1037
01:15:53,345 --> 01:15:55,847
Uncle Hyun-woo's wife
is the owner of our building.

1038
01:15:59,851 --> 01:16:01,395
Let me properly greet you, Aunt.

1039
01:16:01,478 --> 01:16:03,647
-I'm Baek Ho-yeol.
-I see.

1040
01:16:04,523 --> 01:16:06,984
You're my nephew that I only heard about.

1041
01:16:07,067 --> 01:16:08,443
Yes, I am.

1042
01:16:08,527 --> 01:16:10,904
I saw an unfamiliar car
in front of the house.

1043
01:16:10,988 --> 01:16:13,365
Is it yours, Aunt?

1044
01:16:13,448 --> 01:16:14,491
Yes, it is.

1045
01:16:15,826 --> 01:16:17,119
That's sick.

1046
01:16:17,202 --> 01:16:21,248
A V8 engine,
the horsepower and speed tuning.

1047
01:16:21,331 --> 01:16:23,709
That rare car is really yours?

1048
01:16:24,710 --> 01:16:26,545
Could I have a ride, please?

1049
01:16:28,255 --> 01:16:30,799
If I let you, will you stop talking to me?

1050
01:16:31,967 --> 01:16:33,218
I promise you.

1051
01:16:36,513 --> 01:16:38,890
Can you drive him around the village?

1052
01:16:39,474 --> 01:16:42,185
Maybe three or four laps.

1053
01:16:42,269 --> 01:16:43,270
Yes, ma'am.

1054
01:18:37,426 --> 01:18:38,802
My youngest is here!

1055
01:18:39,428 --> 01:18:40,804
Gosh, Hyun-woo.

1056
01:18:40,887 --> 01:18:44,224
The massage chair you gave us last time.

1057
01:18:44,307 --> 01:18:46,560
It's so good. Thank you so much.

1058
01:18:47,686 --> 01:18:51,440
My friends told me to take a picture
with you when I met you.

1059
01:18:51,523 --> 01:18:52,899
Is that okay?

1060
01:18:54,693 --> 01:18:55,944
Two, three.

1061
01:18:56,027 --> 01:18:58,029
I'm sorry, but can you step aside?

1062
01:18:58,113 --> 01:18:59,489
Come on.

1063
01:18:59,573 --> 01:19:00,782
Your arm, too.

1064
01:19:00,866 --> 01:19:02,701
-Even my arm?
-Just the two of us.

1065
01:19:02,784 --> 01:19:07,456
Now, now. He installed air conditioners
and boilers in our senior center.

1066
01:19:07,539 --> 01:19:11,460
Hyun-woo's the pride of Yongdu-ri.
Give him a round of applause!

1067
01:19:12,794 --> 01:19:13,879
He's my brother.

1068
01:19:13,962 --> 01:19:14,963
My brother.

1069
01:19:15,046 --> 01:19:16,047
Eat your fill.

1070
01:19:21,136 --> 01:19:22,387
Well…

1071
01:19:22,471 --> 01:19:25,056
I heard it from your brother and sister.

1072
01:19:25,724 --> 01:19:27,350
But don't worry about me.

1073
01:19:28,101 --> 01:19:30,687
I never mentioned
the divorce to your wife.

1074
01:19:30,771 --> 01:19:32,439
You're mentioning it now, Dad.

1075
01:19:32,522 --> 01:19:33,482
Don't worry.

1076
01:19:34,524 --> 01:19:36,693
She's not here. She's at home.

1077
01:19:37,319 --> 01:19:38,653
-No, she's not.
-What?

1078
01:19:38,737 --> 01:19:40,781
I just picked up Ho-yeol.
She wasn't there.

1079
01:19:41,406 --> 01:19:42,949
What are you talking about?

1080
01:19:43,033 --> 01:19:44,117
She's not there.

1081
01:19:57,339 --> 01:19:58,340
Hello, Mr. Baek.

1082
01:19:58,924 --> 01:20:00,050
Where's Hae-in?

1083
01:20:00,133 --> 01:20:03,678
Is she not at the community hall?
When I came back, she wasn't here.

1084
01:20:22,364 --> 01:20:23,365
Hong Hae-in!

1085
01:20:27,536 --> 01:20:28,370
Hong Hae-in!

1086
01:20:28,453 --> 01:20:29,955
Hae-in!

1087
01:20:33,875 --> 01:20:34,709
Hae-in!

1088
01:20:53,061 --> 01:20:54,062
Hong Hae-in!

1089
01:20:56,314 --> 01:20:57,315
Hae-in!

1090
01:21:14,332 --> 01:21:15,333
Hong Hae-in!

1091
01:22:01,463 --> 01:22:02,297
What happened?

1092
01:22:08,762 --> 01:22:10,722
-Why are you here?
-Why are you yelling?

1093
01:22:14,309 --> 01:22:16,227
I heard you came here out of the blue,

1094
01:22:17,604 --> 01:22:19,564
so I came, but you weren't home

1095
01:22:19,648 --> 01:22:21,733
or at the hall.
No one knew where you were.

1096
01:22:21,816 --> 01:22:23,193
You didn't answer your phone!

1097
01:22:23,985 --> 01:22:24,986
So,

1098
01:22:26,071 --> 01:22:27,989
-why are you here--
-Hold on.

1099
01:22:30,241 --> 01:22:31,576
I came out for a walk.

1100
01:22:34,955 --> 01:22:36,706
A walk in this neighborhood?

1101
01:22:37,374 --> 01:22:38,583
Yes.

1102
01:22:40,877 --> 01:22:42,712
-I was worried!
-Why would you be?

1103
01:22:44,547 --> 01:22:45,840
I'm not a patient.

1104
01:22:49,761 --> 01:22:50,929
Right.

1105
01:22:52,013 --> 01:22:53,974
Yes, you told me that.

1106
01:22:57,394 --> 01:22:58,770
I'm sorry I yelled.

1107
01:23:32,679 --> 01:23:33,722
The truth is…

1108
01:23:35,932 --> 01:23:37,017
I don't remember.

1109
01:23:39,144 --> 01:23:41,396
I don't remember at all why I was there.

1110
01:23:53,533 --> 01:23:55,535
I was in front of your house,

1111
01:23:55,618 --> 01:23:57,787
then suddenly I was somewhere else.

1112
01:24:01,750 --> 01:24:03,668
I don't know when I went there

1113
01:24:06,463 --> 01:24:07,505
or how.

1114
01:24:11,342 --> 01:24:12,343
I have no idea.

1115
01:24:14,971 --> 01:24:15,972
I was…

1116
01:24:21,269 --> 01:24:22,270
so scared.

1117
01:25:44,185 --> 01:25:47,856
NAMED OUTSTANDING SCHOOL OF 2006

1118
01:25:47,939 --> 01:25:49,899
-We're here.
-Okay.

1119
01:25:51,192 --> 01:25:52,819
-See you later.
-See you.

1120
01:25:55,905 --> 01:25:57,115
Wait, Hyun-woo.

1121
01:25:58,449 --> 01:26:01,452
Seoul people aren't that different.
Don't feel discouraged.

1122
01:26:01,536 --> 01:26:03,496
Stand firm.

1123
01:26:03,580 --> 01:26:05,081
-Firm.
-Stand upright.

1124
01:26:05,165 --> 01:26:08,126
And try to glare like this.

1125
01:26:08,209 --> 01:26:10,003
-Okay.
-Good. Go in.

1126
01:26:10,086 --> 01:26:11,421
-Bye, Dad.
-Bye.

1127
01:26:12,172 --> 01:26:14,340
-Listen to your teacher.
-Drive safe!

1128
01:26:21,181 --> 01:26:24,267
Hae-in's going to the States to study.

1129
01:26:24,350 --> 01:26:26,311
Say goodbye to her, okay?

1130
01:26:26,394 --> 01:26:27,937
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

1131
01:26:31,941 --> 01:26:32,942
Look at her face.

1132
01:26:33,776 --> 01:26:35,737
She's still so full of herself.

1133
01:26:35,820 --> 01:26:39,490
There's a rumor that she's
being admitted to a mental hospital.

1134
01:26:40,366 --> 01:26:42,911
I heard it's because she went mad
after her brother died.

1135
01:27:26,037 --> 01:27:27,038
Wait.

1136
01:27:40,009 --> 01:27:41,010
Take it.

1137
01:27:45,306 --> 01:27:46,307
I don't need it.

1138
01:28:03,199 --> 01:28:05,368
Clean it and put some ointment on it.

1139
01:28:17,422 --> 01:28:18,298
Are you crying?

1140
01:28:21,926 --> 01:28:23,136
I'm not.

1141
01:28:34,856 --> 01:28:36,024
You are.

1142
01:28:48,286 --> 01:28:51,205
QUEEN OF TEARS

1143
01:29:18,399 --> 01:29:20,276
Don't you dare mention the divorce.

1144
01:29:20,360 --> 01:29:21,986
You got it.

1145
01:29:22,070 --> 01:29:24,280
Divorce is nothing.

1146
01:29:24,364 --> 01:29:26,074
I wanted to get a divorce too.

1147
01:29:28,409 --> 01:29:29,827
-What's wrong?
-Don't mind me.

1148
01:29:29,911 --> 01:29:31,954
How could their love die?

1149
01:29:32,038 --> 01:29:34,540
They used to be madly in love.

1150
01:29:34,624 --> 01:29:37,543
The woman I love right now is you.

1151
01:29:37,627 --> 01:29:39,504
Your white blood cell count is too low.

1152
01:29:39,587 --> 01:29:41,506
I will find a way.

1153
01:29:41,589 --> 01:29:43,299
Even if I have to search the world,

1154
01:29:43,383 --> 01:29:44,801
I'll find a way to live.

1155
01:29:44,884 --> 01:29:46,427
So I should be…

1156
01:29:46,511 --> 01:29:48,930
by your side at times like this.

1157
01:29:49,013 --> 01:29:49,972
I wanted you

1158
01:29:50,056 --> 01:29:51,724
to be by my side.

1159
01:29:57,313 --> 01:29:59,315
Subtitle translation by: Wayne Ryu
